§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The ❬translate❭ of a subset of a vector space ❬by❭ a given
    vector is the set of all vectors which are the sum of a
    vector in the subset with the given vector. ⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $(V, 𝗙)$ be a vector space. ⦉

  ‖ Let $M ⊂ V$ and $a ∈ V$. ⦉

  ‖ The translate of $M$ by $a$ is the set
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \Set*{x + a}{x ∈ M}, ⦉
    ⦉
    which we denote by $M + a$. ⦉
⦉